added.title: The Robot
added.description: Gumball discovers that Bobert is planning to take over his identity and replace him!

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: The Goons
added.description: Gumball sets out to win his Dad back by winning a blindfolded "dumb" race.

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: The Sock
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are taught confusing lessons about honesty by the school councillor.

added.title: Ralph
added.description: Charlie meets a creature just like him named Ralph. Charlie loves having a new friend, but the Bears think Ralph is bad news.

added.title: Planet Bears
added.description: A nature documentary follows the Bears through their normal routine, which includes a trip to the grocery store.

added.title: Coffee Cave
added.description: After finding out Ice Bear is a master barista, the Bears turn their cave into a popular coffee shop. But it all goes awry when Ice Bear gets too into coffee and goes berserk.

added.title: Charlie's Big Foot
added.description: After Charlie hurts his foot, The Bears have to sneak him into a hospital for medical assistance.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Puffdora's Box
added.description: When Blossom gets overzealous with the spring cleaning, she accidentally unleashes a group of evil spirits.

added.title: Blue Ribbon Blues
added.description: When a famous scientist comes to the school, Blossom will stop at nothing to impress him at the Science Fair even if that means putting Townsville in danger!

added.title: Camping Can Be Cool
added.description: Mordecai tries to prove to Margaret that camping is cool.

added.title: Slam Dunk
added.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

added.title: Cool Bikes
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want cool bikes because if their bikes are cool, then they are cool.

added.title: House Rules
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are sick of Benson's house rules and want to live without them.

added.title: Rap It Up
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby don't want Pops to be called a loser so they say that they'll join him in a rap battle.

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Jeff's New Toy
added.description: Jeff wants to keep his new, flying "Wrath Hover Ginsbot" toy in its box. Clarence is desperate to play with the toy. And poor Sumo is caught in the middle.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Honk
added.description: Seeking to improve his communication skills, Clarence turns to a squeeze horn. It's really annoying.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Mr. Gus Moves Out
added.description: When a fed-up Mr. Gus moves out of the RV, Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve work together to get him back.

removed.title: Skips Strikes
removed.description: Skips reveals himself to be an excellent bowler, until he realizes he has to bowl Death's team.

removed.title: Inventor Mentor
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

removed.title: Princess Buttercup
removed.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

removed.title: The End
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced that the world will end in 24 hours.

removed.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
removed.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

removed.title: Bet to Be Blonde
removed.description: Rigby wins a bet with Mordecai and makes him get a blonde perm.

removed.title: In the House
removed.description: Rigby eggs the wrong house and gets cursed by a wizard.

removed.title: Money Broom Wizard
removed.description: Can Clarence, Jeff and Sumo manage to have a good time at "Pizza Swamp" Arcade with only one dollar to spend between them? Yes.

removed.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
removed.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

removed.title: Escape from Monster Island
removed.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

removed.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
removed.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

removed.title: RV Olympics
removed.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus compete in the RV Olympics.

removed.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
removed.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

removed.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
removed.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

removed.title: Lost in the Supermarket
removed.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

removed.title: Professor Lampwick
removed.description: Chloe's professor is too mean to give her any face time to talk over her poor grade. The Bears take things into their own hands to help, causing big trouble for Chloe.

removed.title: Subway
removed.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

removed.title: Painbow
removed.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

removed.title: Creepy Doll/Death Metal Crash Pit
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby discover an old Victorian Doll that Pop's has not played with or seen since he was a child and unwittingly unleash its pent up rage against him.  Muscle Man and High Five Ghost want to crash an old RV into a pit, but it's haunted by an 80s death metal band.

removed.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
removed.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

removed.title: Neighbors
removed.description: Some new neighbors set up camp next to the Bears' cave. Panda and Ice love it, but Grizz thinks they're up to no good.

removed.title: The Debt
removed.description: Gumball resolves to save Mr Robinson's life during Elmore's Senior Talent Show.

removed.title: The Responsible
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

removed.title: Dinosaur Day
removed.description: Pizza Steve's jealousy ruins Uncle Grandpa's Dinosaur Day celebration for Mr. Gus.

removed.title: The DVD
removed.description: Gumball is desperate to avoid a late fee on the rented dvd he accidentally destroyed.

removed.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
removed.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

removed.title: The Third
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

removed.title: The Stayover
removed.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

removed.title: Panda's Friend
removed.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.

removed.title: Uncle Melvins
removed.description: Legendary rock band, the Melvins, team up with Uncle Grandpa to help a young girl who wants to win her school's talent show.

removed.title: Clarence's Millions
removed.description: When Clarence realizes the classroom "buddy star" system is leaving some kids behind, he creates his own form of currency called "Clarence Dollars." The new reward system promptly turns the entire school upside down.

removed.title: Jerky Jasper
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to great lengths to meet Pizza Steve's imaginary friend.

removed.title: Stick Hockey
removed.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.
